org.locationtech.geowave.core.ingest.spi

Interface IngestFormatPluginProviderSpi<I,O>

  • Type Parameters:
    I - The type for intermediate data
    O - The type for the resulting data that is ingested into GeoWave
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractSimpleFeatureIngestFormat, GDELTIngestFormat, GeoLifeIngestFormat, GeoToolsRasterDataStoreIngestFormat, GeoToolsVectorDataStoreIngestFormat, GeoWaveAvroIngestFormat, GpxIngestFormat, Stanag4676IngestFormat, TdriveIngestFormat, TwitterIngestFormat

    public interface IngestFormatPluginProviderSpi<I,O>
    This interface can be injected and automatically discovered using SPI to provide a new ingest format to the GeoWave ingestion framework. It is not required that a new ingest format implement all of the plugins. However, each plugin directly corresponds to a user selected operation and only the plugins that are supported will result in usable operations.

      • getIngestFormatName

        String getIngestFormatName()
        This will represent the name for the format that is registered with the ingest framework and presented as a data format option via the commandline. For consistency, this name is preferably lower-case and without spaces, and should uniquely identify the data format as much as possible.
        Returns:
        The name that will be associated with this format

      • createOptionsInstances

        IngestFormatOptions createOptionsInstances()
        This is a means for a plugin to provide custom command-line options. If this is null, there will be no custom options added.
        Returns:
        The ingest format's option provider or null for no custom options

      • getIngestFormatDescription

        String getIngestFormatDescription()
        This is a user-friendly full description of the data format that this plugin provider supports. It will be presented to the command-line user as help when the registered data formats are listed.
        Returns:
        The user-friendly full description for this data format

      • createAvroFormatPlugin

        GeoWaveAvroFormatPlugin<I,O> createAvroFormatPlugin(IngestFormatOptions options)
                                             throws UnsupportedOperationException
        This plugin will be used by the ingestion framework to stage intermediate data from a local filesystem (for example to HDFS for map reduce ingest or to kafka for kafka ingest).
        Returns:
        The plugin for staging to avro if it is supported
        Throws:
        UnsupportedOperationException - If staging data is not supported (generally this implies that ingesting using map-reduce or kafka will not be supported)
